<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-04-13T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-04-13T18:00:00-05:00" n="1055" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1055">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/2783a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Armour</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-13T18:00:00-05:00">April 13, 1929—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>109. For Young.</p>
                        <p>Press carries report that figures on reparations will be given out
                            Monday. Complete statement of this Government’s position will be
                            telegraphed you tomorrow, and it is hoped that there may be no publicity
                            until after you have had opportunity to consider statement. I may add
                            that Mr. Wilson’s letter of April 12 to you correctly states position of
                            this Government respecting mixed claims and Army costs.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>